# RFID Inventory — Project Context

## What this is
Warehouse inventory web app driven by a UHF RFID handheld. FastAPI backend
(`app.py`) + SQLite (`db.py`), single-page browser UI (`static/`), serial
worker thread for the reader (`reader.py`). Modes: check-in, check-out,
sweep & count, warehouse browse, tag finder. Bills of lading are scanned
(Epson ES-50 via the NAPS2 CLI, `scanner.py`), OCRed, and BOL#/PO#/vendor
auto-extracted (`bol_extract.py`). `rfid_inventory.py` is a legacy CLI kept
only as reference; the old Google Sheets backend is gone.

## Hardware facts (not discoverable from code alone)
- Reader: Vulcan RFID Indium = rebadged TSL 1128. Protocol: TSL ASCII 2.0
  over USB serial (classic-Bluetooth SPP is unreliable; avoid).
- Commands are `.xx` + args, CR/LF-terminated (`.iv` inventory, `.ws` write
  single transponder). Responses are line-based: `EP:` per-tag EPC hex,
  `RI:` RSSI, `SW:` trigger state, terminated by `OK:` or `ER: nnn`.
- The physical trigger drives scans (the reader runs `.iv` itself; the app
  never polls). A scan burst is finalized after a quiet gap
  (`QUIET_GAP_SECONDS`); parameters are set with `-n` (no action) commands.
- UHF dedup principle: a tag is read many times per second — NEVER count
  raw reads. Collect distinct EPCs; one EPC == one physical box.

## Packaging / platforms
- Windows .exe via PyInstaller (`RFIDInventory.spec`, `build-windows.bat`).
  Per-machine overrides live in `settings.ini` next to the exe; defaults in
  `config.py` (note the frozen-build path split: bundled assets vs.
  persistent data next to the executable).
- Development happens on macOS; the serial port is auto-detected with a
  `settings.ini` override.

## Current direction (July 2026)
- Offline-first: the .exe + SQLite is the source of truth. A `cloud/`
  FastAPI app on Azure (App Service + Azure PostgreSQL,
  switch-warehouse.brasfieldgorrie.com) mirrors inventory read-only and
  queues material requests; the .exe syncs via an outbound
  `POST /sync/exchange` worker. Databricks is intentionally not used.
- Label printing: Zebra ZD621R (300 dpi, 4x6" RFID labels) prints and
 encodes app-minted EPCs at check-in, raw ZPL over TCP 9100 (`printer.py`;
 `printer_host` in settings.ini). Program position / write power live in
 the printer via its RFID Calibrate — never send `^RS`/`^LL` from the app.
 The handheld's `.ws` write path is no longer planned.
- Later phases: stale-stock aging flags; a staged checkout state so exit
 staging and sweeps don't conflict.

## Conventions
- Raw SQL house style in `db.py` (no ORM); keep dependencies minimal.
- Confirm reader behavior against real hardware before trusting parsing
  changes; "Test without hardware" in the UI injects fake EPCs.
